First, let's find A △ B and B △ A.

A △ B is the symmetric difference between sets A and B, which means we take the elements that are in either A or B, but not in both. 

A △ B = {1, 4}

Similarly, B △ A is the symmetric difference between sets B and A.

B △ A = {1, 4}

Now we need to find (A △ B) △ (B △ A).

(A △ B) △ (B △ A) = {1, 4} △ {1, 4}

Since both sets have the same elements, their symmetric difference will be an empty set, as there are no elements that are in one set but not in the other.

(A △ B) △ (B △ A) = ∅
